&lt;P&gt;Optimization is probably the most overused word in management today. But, what is optimization? The Concise Oxford Dictionary defines optimization as: âthe most favorable condition; the best compromise between opposing tendencies; best or most favorableâ1. Before exploring the implications of that definition, letâs go back and understand MRO (maintenance, repair and operations) inventory.&lt;/P&gt;
